Disk Lens – A PowerShell WPF Disk Analyzer for Windows
Disk Lens is a free, open-source tool for Windows that helps you visualize and clean up disk space. No installation needed – just a single PowerShell script.
I came up with the idea and the requirements for this tool, but I want to be transparent: the entire codebase was written by Claude (Anthropic's AI assistant). Every line of PowerShell, the WPF GUI, the parallel scan engine, the duplicate finder, the empty folder finder – all of it was generated through an iterative back-and-forth where I described what I wanted and Claude implemented it.
I think that kind of transparency matters, especially in open source. The idea was mine. The code was Claude's. The result is something I'm genuinely happy with and wanted to share.
What it does:

Parallel folder scan with live updates and size class visualization
Built-in file browser with breadcrumb navigation and async size calculation
Duplicate file finder (three-stage MD5 algorithm)
Empty folder finder
Real-time drive, Recycle Bin and Temp status bar
Full English / German UI with live language switch
Dark theme, no installation, single .ps1 file

Requirements: Windows 10/11, PowerShell 5.1+ (pre-installed)
powershellpowershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File DiskLens.ps1
